###when i need to write class in python, follow the form like this:

class unit:
    def func1(self,val1,val2):
        ...
        return a
    def func2(self,...):
        ...
        return b
    def func3(self,...) :
        ...
        return c

###if i need to call function of this class(func1 for example) outside the class, i shall do this:

unit=unit()
unit.func1(val1,val2)

###if i need to call function of this class inside the class, i shall do this:

self.func1(val1,val2)
